==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yakin
<hw>Ya"kin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
large Asiatic antelope (<spn>Budorcas taxicolor</spn>) native of the
higher parts of the Himalayas and other lofty mountains. Its head and
neck resemble those of the ox, and its tail is like that of the goat.
Called also <altname>budorcas</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yakoots</ent>⟦br⟧
